parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to catch fire, even when parked and unattended, resulting in damage to property and potentially harming occupants.
symptoms: Smoke or flames emitting from the dashboard
and the vehicle catching fire while parked or driven.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to catch fire, even when parked and unattended, resulting in damage to property and potentially harming occupants.
symptoms: Smoke or flames emitting from the ignition switch
and the vehicle catching fire while parked or driven.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speed control deactivation switch can cause the vehicle to catch fire, even when parked and unattended, resulting in damage to property and potentially harming occupants.
symptoms: Smoke or flames emitting from the speed control deactivation switch
and the vehicle catching fire while parked or driven.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the anti-theft alarm system can cause unnecessary noise and disturbance, leading to annoyance and potential safety issues.
symptoms: The anti-theft alarm system goes off at random times
even when no apparent reason is present.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the speed control deactivation switch can cause an underhood fire, which can lead to vehicle damage, personal injury, or even fatalities.
symptoms: with the fire originating from the speed control deactivation switch; the cruise control switch fails to work or works intermittently; the vehicle accelerates on its own; the brakes fail to engage; a hollowing noise is heard from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Repair of Speed Control Deactivation Switch
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inadequate repair of the speed control deactivation switch can lead to continued safety risks, including the possibility of an underhood fire.
symptoms: The dealer fails to repair the vehicle properly
citing unavailability of parts or providing unsatisfactory explanations; the consumer receives multiple recall notices with no resolution.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the brake system can cause extended stopping distances, loss of brake power, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: brake pedal goes to the floor

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rupture of the fuel line can cause fuel leaks, fires, and explosions, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
Failure of the cruise control system can cause unintended acceleration, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, which can lead to injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Cruise control does not turn off

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to catch fire, leading to a total loss of the vehicle and potentially causing injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: smoke and flames engulfing the vehicle
squeaking sounds from under the hood.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Head gasket failure can cause coolant leaks, engine damage, and potentially lead to engine failure.
Oil pan gasket failure can cause oil leaks, leading to engine damage and potentially causing accidents.

Engine noise and stalling can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents.
